article.headline: Brown 90, Stony Brook 79
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Pat Powers was 10-of-13 from the field, including 3-of-5 from 3-point range, and scored 25 points as Brown stopped a five-game losing streak with a 90-79 victory over Stony Brook on Tuesday night. Jason Forte added 23 points for the Bears (3-7). Mitchell Beauford had 22 points for the Seawolves (3-6), who lost their third straight, while Mike Popoko added 17. Mike Konopka scored all the points as Stony Brook opened the game with a 7-0 run. The Bears, behind two 3-pointers by Luke Ruscoe and five points from Forte, responded with a 21-8 run. A 3 by Popoko got the Seawolves within 21-18, but Powers hit two straight jumpers as Brown took its largest lead of the half, 29-18, with 5:32 to go. C.J. Munirs jumper got Stony Brook as close as 39-34, but Brown broke the game open with a 21-7 run. Powers scored 13 points, including two 3-pointers, in the burst as the Bears went up 60-41 with 11:03 to play.
